<article id="post-616" class="post-616 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-technology tag-content-management">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/02/keynote-at-summit-2007/" rel="bookmark">Keynote at Summit 2007</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I have no idea who the guy is on the stage. He came out after a Harold Faltermeyer-esque opening movie (complete with Windows system click sound at the end) and started talking. No introduction whatsoever.<br />
John Shackleton has now taken the stage. Older guy. I&#8217;m vaguely curious to know how long this guy has been with OpenText. Claims OpenText is now the largest independent ECM vendor.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/02/keynote-at-summit-2007/#more-616" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Keynote at Summit 2007&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

