<article id="post-612" class="post-612 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-technology">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/01/bathroom-humour-in-domain-names/" rel="bookmark">Bathroom humour in domain names</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I&#8217;m in the process of updating the IPs for a whack of domain names and realized something about some of the top-level (and second-level) domains out there. Some of them, at least in English, were chosen really poorly:</p>
<ul>
<li>bj</li>
<li>bo</li>
<li>bs</li>
<li>co.ma</li>
<li>com.et</li>
</ul>
<p> <a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/01/bathroom-humour-in-domain-names/#more-612" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Bathroom humour in domain names&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
